steps.name: Artifact
steps.description: Many types of Artifacts can be detected

steps.name: Input Files
steps.description:
Add your files, select .edf, .sts or .eeg files.

 European Data Format : .edf and .tsv are mandatory. The .tsv must includes the sleep stages.

Stellate : .sig and .sts files are mandatory. The .sts must includes the sleep stages.

NATUS : the whole NATUS subject folder is mandatory. The .ent must includes the sleep stages.

Select the montage and the channels to detect the artifact on.

The Alias are needed to distinguish EEG channels from EMG channels.

EMG channels are only used to enhance the muscle artifact detection.

Make sure to add the selected channels into the Alias.

Only one EMG channel is sufficient.

*If you want to run the artifact detection without EMG channel, just type 'EMG' in the EMG Alias.
